Rating: 4
I first made this for vegan company and was completely blown away. Since then, I've probably made it at least a dozen times. I can't be happy until I find an easier way to do everything, so I usually used canned diced tomatoes and canned chickpeas (then adjust salt just before eating!), couscous from a box, and more ras el hanout. I also roast the almonds rather than frying them. Found what I think is a good ras el hanout blend and harissa by ordering online at The Spice House. These really make the dish! Next time I'll try wine and potatoes, as some reviewers have suggested. Made it once with bok choy instead of cabbage and it was lovely.

