Rating: 4
so flavorful and well-balanced. not nearly as complicated as i thought. i used barley couscous out of the box, cooked separately, and did the stew in a 4-quart saucepan. next time i'll just do it in my 5-quart cocotte because it was a little tight in there. i cooked it partially covered, per the recipe, and only used half the water, substituting 1 of the cups with white wine. perfect. this dish is officially added to my repertoire.

Rating: 4
Not as complicated as it sounds if you just make the broth and vegetables, and then use couscous out of a box, which only takes 5 minutes to cook.

