I made this recipe with my former roommate who grew up in Algeria - he referred to this recipe as "Moroccan Cous Cous". Simply speaking, this is my #1 favourite vegan recipe ever! I have been vegan for almost 1 1/2 years and I love to cook, :)

Rating: 3
What a unique recipe. I'm not really sure I cooked it correctly and I had to make adjustments as I didn't have the correct pan. I didn't think that the stew portion was adequately seasoned, however; when you put everything in a bowl, added the harissa, almonds and onions a fasinating event happen in relationship to flavour and texture. I found the dish very creative and enjoyed learning about so many new uses of spices. I will definitely be investigating the ethnic origins of this recipe and doing a little further experimenting.